{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3691064,"name":"Maya","username":"mapemaya","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/mapemaya/{size}/267073_2.png","created_at":"2025-07-27T14:17:13.635Z","cooked":"<p>Hi, I’m kind of new to replay watch and have never successfully used it before.</p>
<p>I followed the documentation as closely as I could, one weird thing is that I have Windows on my computer but for some reason, while the replay watch command for mac/linux worked the one for windows didn’t (it didn’t recognize the command) but ok it ran eventually.</p>
<p>The issue is replay watch runs, a new log is created but it never finishes. Its stuck on “Replay Active” no matter what I do, and as a result it never updates the log in advantage scope (thus defeating the whole point of replay watch).</p>
<p>Regular replay works for me perfectly… Here is the relevant code</p>
<p><strong>Robot.java</strong></p>
<p><em>package frc.robot;</em></p>
<p><em>import org.littletonrobotics.junction.LogFileUtil;</em><br>
<em>import org.littletonrobotics.junction.LoggedRobot;</em><br>
<em>import org.littletonrobotics.junction.Logger;</em><br>
<em>import org.littletonrobotics.junction.networktables.NT4Publisher;</em><br>
<em>import org.littletonrobotics.junction.wpilog.WPILOGReader;</em><br>
<em>import org.littletonrobotics.junction.wpilog.WPILOGWriter;</em><br>
<em>import org.littletonrobotics.junction.wpilog.WPILOGWriter.AdvantageScopeOpenBehavior;</em></p>
<p><em>import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.Command;</em><br>
<em>import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.CommandScheduler;</em><br>
<em>import frc.robot.Constants.RunMode;</em></p>
<p><em>public class Robot extends LoggedRobot {</em></p>
<pre><code>private Command m_autonomousCommand;

private final RobotContainer m_robotContainer;

public static RunMode runMode = RunMode.REAL;

public Robot() {
    Logger.recordMetadata("2025-Season-Code", "Robot-Code"); // Set a metadata value

    if (!isReal()) {
        runMode = RunMode.SIMULATION;
        runReplay();
        setUseTiming(false);
    }
    initLogging();


    Logger.start(); // Start logging! No more data receivers, replay sources, or metadata values may be added.

    m_robotContainer = new RobotContainer();
    System.out.println(runMode);


}

public void runReplay() {
    runMode = RunMode.REPLAY;
    String logPath = "C:/Users/Maya Lev/Desktop/2025-Offseason/2025-Offseason/logs/akit_25-07-25_15-42-50.wpilog"; // Pull the replay log from AdvantageScope (or prompt the user)
    Logger.setReplaySource(new WPILOGReader(logPath)); // Read replay log
    Logger.addDataReceiver(new WPILOGWriter(LogFileUtil.addPathSuffix(logPath, "_sim"), AdvantageScopeOpenBehavior.ALWAYS)); // Save outputs to a new log

}

public void initLogging() {
    Logger.addDataReceiver(new NT4Publisher());
    Logger.addDataReceiver(new WPILOGWriter()); 
}
</code></pre>
<p><strong>(I have an IO Interface in my code as shown on the advantage kit documentation)</strong></p>
<p><strong>My subsystem class:</strong></p>
